CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 9, 1950, pg. 17 reads: "Shut-Ins Remembered at Leech Farm - More than 450 patients were recently made happy when representatives from the Young People's Department of the Women's Missionary Society made, and presented to them, favors.  The group has been distributing the tokens of good will for four years...Left, lower photo: Men patients are remembered, too.  Pictured, left to right: Misses Patricia Barbour, Lois Glass, Paula Sulivan, Sylvia Harris, Nada Turner, Mrs. Alice Glass, Misses Bernice Barrow, Vivian Green, Lou Pearl Page, Ada Barbour, Frank Toseano and John Williams...-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of the Young People's Department of the Women's Missionary Society, left to right: Patricia Barbour, Lois Glass, Paula Sulivan, Sylvia Harris, Nada Turner, Alice Glass, Bernice Barrow, Vivian Green, Lou Pearl Page, and Ada Barbour, presenting gifts to patients Frank Toseano and John Williams, at Leech Farm
